verbose_text: At < = 400 degreesC, desorbed hydrogen is defined by BS ISO 3690 standards [XREF_BIBR] as diffusible hydrogen, elevated temperatures> 400 degreesC being used to measure strongly trapped residual hydrogen, and this is in contrast to the Australian standard for example that defines significant amounts of residual hydrogen are released> 150 degreesC [XREF_BIBR].
